tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly low HbA1c and fasting glucose, which may suggest hypoglycemia or recent changes in glycemic control. Chloride is slightly elevated, possibly indicating mild dehydration, metabolic acidosis, or laboratory variation. Renal function, electrolytes, and other parameters are within normal limits. Clinical correlation is recommended.
